A Nomura Holdings Inc. employee was
found dead last month in Singapore where he was studying abroad,
the Yomiuri newspaper reported, citing Japanâ€™s Ministry of
Foreign Affairs.  The body had multiple bruises and Singapore police are
investigating, the Yomiuri said, citing the ministry. The
employee, on a Nomura internal study abroad program, was found
lying on the ground on the morning on Oct. 23 and confirmed dead
at a hospital that afternoon, the report said. The body has been
returned to Japan, it said.  Keiko Sugai, a Nomura spokeswoman in Tokyo, was not
